parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column lock can cause the steering wheel to seize or lock, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel seizes or locks
the steering wheel will not turn
the power steering warning light illuminates
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
the column lock warning light illuminates
the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECL system can cause the steering column lock to malfunction, leading to the steering wheel seizing or locking, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel seizes or locks
the power steering warning light illuminates
the column lock warning light illuminates
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
the ECL system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the recall repair to properly address the steering column lock issue can lead to continued problems with the steering system, potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering column lock issue persists after recall repair
the steering wheel seizes or locks
the power steering warning light illuminates
the column lock warning light illuminates
the vehicle stalls or shuts off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat frame can cause the seat to move unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The driver's seat slides forward and backward without warning
the seat moves when the brake pedal is depressed
the seat moves when the accelerator is pressed
the seat does not lock in position
the seat moves about 1-2 inches during acceleration and braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Electronic Column Lock (ECL) can cause the steering wheel to lock, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel locks up
the vehicle stalls
the "Service Steering Wheel Lock" message appears on the DIC
the vehicle cannot be moved
and the safety feature is bypassed
leaving the car vulnerable to theft.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Brake Traction Control Module (EBTCM) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EBTCM can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, lose traction, and fail to slow down, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the traction control and ABS warning indicators illuminate
the brake pedal is depressed
and the vehicle fails to slow down until the gear is shifted into park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system issues can cause fuel leaks, odors, and engine stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuel odor
fuel leaks
engine stalling
and incorrect fuel level readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience electrical failures, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
electrical failures
and battery acid leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks and electrical failures can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience electrical failures, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Water leaks
electrical failures
and engine stalling.
